# Rate Limiting sur POST /token (SEC003)

## Protection brute-force
- Limite : 5 tentatives par IP / 15 min
- Fallback : exponential backoff après 3 failures

## Implémentation CI4
```php
// app/Filters/RateLimitFilter.php
if ($request->getPath() === 'token' && $request->getMethod() === 'post') {
    $ip = $request->getIPAddress();
    $attempts = $cache->get("oauth_attempts_{$ip}") ?? 0;
    if ($attempts >= 5) {
        return $this->respond(429, ['error' => 'Too many requests']);
    }
}
```

## Storage
- Redis (production) ou Cache File (dev)
- Configurable en `.env`

# Migrations CI4 (ARCH011)

## Convention
- Expand/Contract pour breaking changes
- Jamais de `DROP COLUMN` direct
- Step 1 : ajouter colonne, deployer code reader
- Step 2 : deployer writer (popule colonne)
- Step 3 : (optionnel) cleanup ancienne colonne après 1 semaine

## Exemple : task.org_id
```php
// Migration 1 : Expand
$forge->addColumn('tasks', ['org_id' => ['type' => 'BIGINT', 'null' => true]]);

// Code : TaskModel::save() populate org_id

// Migration 2 : Contract
$forge->modifyColumn('tasks', ['org_id' => ['null' => false]]);
$forge->addForeignKey('tasks', 'org_id', 'organizations', 'id');

// Migration 3 : Cleanup (après 1 week)
$forge->dropColumn('tasks', 'user_id');
```

# Event → Palace Indexing

## Flow async (EVENT-PALACE-001)
1. `TaskCreated` dispatché synchrone
2. Queue Worker reçoit async
3. MemPalace adapter appelé
4. Wing créé : `task.uuid` + title
5. Drawer base : "Task created"

## Prérequis
- PALACE-001 : MemPalace HTTP adapter
- PALACE-002 : UUID task ↔ palace link
- ASYNC001 : Queue infrastructure

## Code
```php
// app/Events/TaskCreated.php
public $uuid, $title;

// app/Listeners/PalaceIndexListener.php
public function handle(TaskCreated $event) {
    // Queue async job → MemPalace adapter
    $this->queue->enqueue('PalaceIndexJob', ['uuid' => $event->uuid, 'title' => $event->title]);
}
```

# Integration Tests — vraie DB

## Contenu
- Queries Repository → valident aggrégation / joins
- Endpoints REST → valident routing + filtres + réponse JSON
- Workflows entiers : créer task → assigner → marquer done → palace créé

## Signal d'alerte
Tous les tests d'un flow mockent le même endpoint → créer test intégration réel

## Prérequis
- PostgreSQL local ou Docker
- Seeds de base (users, projects) — chargées avant each test
- Rollback après each test (transactions)

## Convention
```php
// tests/integration/TaskControllerTest.php
class TaskControllerTest extends CIUnitTestCase {
    protected function setUp(): void {
        $this->db->transBegin();
        $this->seedBase(); // users, projects
    }

    protected function tearDown(): void {
        $this->db->transRollback();
    }
}
```
